medy]]\" by [[Seether]] (52) (tie) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/seether/chart-history/hot-mainstream-rock-tracks/song/477205|title=Seether Remedy Chart History|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509001144/https://www.billboard.com/music/seether/chart-history/hot-mainstream-rock-tracks/song/477205|archivedate=2018-05-09}}</ref>\n*\"[[Life Is Beautiful (Sixx:A.M. song)|Life Is Beautiful]]\" by [[Sixx: A.M.]] (52) (tie) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/sixx-am/chart-history/hot-mainstream-rock-tracks/song/530800|title=Sixx: A.M. Life Is Beautiful Chart History|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509001145/https://www.billboard.com/music/sixx-am/chart-history/hot-mainstream-rock-tracks/song/530800|archivedate=2018-05-09}}</ref>\n\n<!--This section has had more than enough time to be corrected. Commenting out.\n===Songs with ten or more weeks at number one===\n{{unreferenced section|date=June 2016}}\n'''21 weeks'''\n*\"[[Loser (3 Doors Down song)|Loser]]\" by [[3 Doors Down]] (2000\u201301)\n'''20 weeks'''\n*\"[[It's Been Awhile]]\" by [[Staind]] (2001)\n'''17 weeks'''\n*\"[[Higher (Creed song)|Higher]]\" by [[Creed (band)|Creed]] (1999\u20132000)\n*\"[[When I'm Gone (3 Doors Down song)|When I'm Gone]]\" by [[3 Doors Down]] (2002\u201303)\n'''16 weeks'''\n*\"[[Touch, Peel and Stand]]\" by [[Days of the New]] (1997)\n'''15 weeks'''\n*\"[[Interstate Love Song]]\" by [[Stone Temple Pilots]] (1994)\n*\"[[Heavy (Collective Soul song)|Heavy]]\" by [[Collective Soul]] (1999)\n'''14 weeks'''\n*\"[[So Far Away (Staind song)|So Far Away]]\" by [[Staind]] (2003)\n*\"[[Boulevard of Broken Dreams (Green Day song)|Boulevard of Broken Dreams]]\" by [[Green Day]] (2005)\n*\"[[Fake It (Seether Song)|Fake It]]\" by [[Seether]] (2007\u201308)\n*\"[[Inside the Fire (Disturbed song)|Inside the Fire]]\" by [[Disturbed (band)|Disturbed]] (2008)\n'''13 weeks'''\n*\"[[Start Me Up]]\" by [[The Rolling Stone